What you need to know:

Bt cotton seeds are developed to kill the African bollworm, which is responsible for up to 100 per cent crop loss.Bt cotton matures a month earlier than conventional cotton and produces many more bolls. Experts also say the GM variety can produce up to 1,200 kilos an acre while conventional cotton can yield as low as 200.Kenya last year approved commercial farming of Bt Cotton, and in April, the Ministry of Agriculture distributed one metric tonne of Bt cotton seeds for planting on demonstration plots and raised awareness on the transgenic cotton varieties.Cotton is grown in 24 out of Kenyaâ€™s 47 devolved regions, even though less than 10 have put the crop in their strategic plans.